1) Site wykop.pl because the bug found and highly reproducible here

2) Add custom CSS to page (Stylish?)

// Split main content element into columns
section > *  { -moz-column-count: 2 }

// Remove sidebar (for research purpose) because it gets in the way
aside { display: none !important; }
section > * { margin-right: 0px !important }

// Hide some random articles (emulate Adblock Plus)
article:nth-of-type(3n+2) { display: none !important; }

3) (optional) disable JS for research purpose
(reflow is not triggerd by any script)

4) The hard part. The bug isn't easy reproducible. Hover over elements labelled "wykop" (eng: 'digg') for applied "shadow on hover" effect. You will have to try hovering over different elements and with different page widths (resize browser widnow).
The effect does not resize <article> box dimensions but still at some point <articles> will reflow between column layout. Since this is :hover effect and position of element changes its possible to trigger constant back and forth reflow (until fx crash).

Also can be reproduced by hovering over "zakop" elements (eng: 'bury') that shows absolutly positioned menu (doesn't change <article> dimension also) with bury reasons. This element is visible to logged in users on wykop.pl/wykopalisko

todo: better site-example

